'''Birkdale''' is a [[suburb]] of [[Auckland]], [[New Zealand]]. The population was 6,798 in the [[New Zealand Census of Population and Dwellings|2006 Census]], an increase of 429 from 2001.<ref>The population is the sum of the statistical areas of Birkdale North ({{NZ Quickstats|3510210|Birkdale North}}) and Birkdale South ({{NZ Quickstats|3510220|Birkdale South}})</ref> The suburb is in the North Shore ward, one of the thirteen administrative divisions of Auckland City.
==Education== Birkenhead College is a secondary (years 9-13) school with a [[Socio-Economic Decile|decile rating]] of 6 and a roll of 869.<ref>{{TKI|31|Birkenhead College}}</ref> The school began as Birkdale College, opening in 1972.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.birkenhead.school.nz/school/history.htm|title=History|publisher=Birkenhead College}}</ref>
Birkdale Intermediate is an intermediate (years 7-8) school with a decile rating of 6 and a roll of 457.<ref>{{TKI|1228|Birkdale Intermediate}}</ref>
Birkdale North School and Birkdale Primary School are contributing primary (years 1-6) schools with decile ratings of 4 and 5, and rolls of 142<ref>{{TKI|1229|Birkdale North School}}</ref> and 278,<ref>{{TKI|1230|Birkdale Primary School}}</ref> respectively. Birkdale Primary was established in 1894.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://birkdaleprimary.school.nz/?page_id=4|title=About Us|publisher=Birkdale Primary School|accessdate=2009-01-11}}</ref>
All these schools are coeducational.
